{
  "documentVersion": "1.1",
  "layout": {
    "pageSize": {
      "width": 600,
      "height": 800
    },
    "margins": {
      "top": 50,
      "right": 50,
      "bottom": 50,
      "left": 50
    },
    "fontFamily": "Arimo",
    "fontSize": 10,
    "lineHeight": 1.4,
    "pageBackground": "#fcfbf7"
  },
  "fonts": {
    "regular": "Arimo",
    "bold": "Arimo"
  },
  "styles": {
    "h1": {
      "fontSize": 24,
      "fontWeight": "bold",
      "marginBottom": 12,
      "keepWithNext": true,
      "color": "#233b56"
    },
    "h2": {
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontWeight": "bold",
      "marginBottom": 8,
      "keepWithNext": true,
      "color": "#33577d"
    },
    "p": {
      "marginBottom": 8
    },
    "sidebar-label": {
      "fontSize": 9,
      "fontWeight": "bold",
      "marginBottom": 4,
      "color": "#555555"
    },
    "sidebar-body": {
      "fontSize": 9,
      "marginBottom": 6,
      "color": "#333333"
    }
  },
  "elements": [
    {
      "type": "h1",
      "content": "Zone Map: Absolute Rock Actor"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "This proof places a visible rock actor at explicit map coordinates inside the main zone. Ordinary labels should negotiate around that fixed body rather than treating it like an in-flow document block."
    },
    {
      "type": "zone-map",
      "properties": {
        "style": {
          "marginTop": 12,
          "marginBottom": 12
        }
      },
      "zones": [
        {
          "id": "main",
          "elements": [
            {
              "type": "h2",
              "content": "Main Zone"
            },
            {
              "type": "field-actor",
              "content": "",
              "properties": {
                "spatialField": {
                  "kind": "exclude",
                  "x": 92,
                  "y": 76,
                  "wrap": "around",
                  "gap": 8,
                  "exclusionAssembly": {
                    "members": [
                      { "shape": "circle", "x": 0, "y": 34, "w": 74, "h": 74 },
                      { "shape": "circle", "x": 54, "y": 6, "w": 90, "h": 90 },
                      { "shape": "rect", "x": 44, "y": 54, "w": 88, "h": 28 },
                      { "shape": "circle", "x": 120, "y": 56, "w": 36, "h": 36 }
                    ]
                  }
                },
                "style": {
                  "width": 156,
                  "backgroundColor": "#f8f6ef",
                  "height": 116
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "p",
              "content": "A placed rock actor should feel like a thing that exists on the map first, not a paragraph decoration. The first label immediately yields to that occupied territory."
            },
            {
              "type": "p",
              "content": "Because the body is anchored by explicit x and y coordinates, later labels are negotiating around a field that lives in space, not one that merely follows document order."
            },
            {
              "type": "p",
              "content": "That makes this proof useful for future game-oriented contexts too. A rock, creature, hazard, or sleeping dragon can be an actor with presence while the zone itself remains only a region."
            },
            {
              "type": "p",
              "content": "If this idea is honest, the visible circles should stay recognizable and the surrounding labels should divide into multiple scanline slots instead of pretending the map is a rigid column."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "sidebar",
          "elements": [
            {
              "type": "sidebar-label",
              "content": "MAP NOTE"
            },
            {
              "type": "sidebar-body",
              "content": "The rock is absolute only within the main zone's local world. The sidebar continues independently and should not react."
            },
            {
              "type": "sidebar-label",
              "content": "WHY IT MATTERS"
            },
            {
              "type": "sidebar-body",
              "content": "This is the cleaner world-facing proof: one actor exists in space and neighboring actors flow around it."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "zoneLayout": {
        "columns": [
          {
            "mode": "flex",
            "fr": 2
          },
          {
            "mode": "flex",
            "fr": 1
          }
        ],
        "gap": 16
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "Content below the zone-map resumes in normal document flow after the absolute rock proof."
    }
  ]
}
